.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [ scriptfile ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a minimal UNIX command interpreter that executes commands read from standard input or a script file.
.PP
The shell supports execution of standard UNIX commands, built-in commands (\fBexit\fP, \fBenv\fP), and command arguments. It runs in both interactive and non-interactive modes.
.SH OPTIONS
No options are supported.
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Display the environment variables.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Interactive mode:
.B
$ ./simple_shell
.TP
Non-interactive mode:
.B
$ echo "ls -l" | ./simple_shell
.SH AUTHORS
Ahmed Cisse, Mahamat Abdalllah Moussa, Patrice Bolin
.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1)
